  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "\"The Rainbow,\" by William Wordsworth (1770-1850), accords with every child's feelings. It voices the spirit of all ages that would love to imagine it \"a bridge to heaven.\""
  },
  {
    "tag": "pre",
    "innerHtml": "<code>My heart leaps up when I behold  \nA rainbow in the sky;  \nSo was it when my life began,  \nSo is it now I am a man,  \nSo be it when I shall grow old,  \nOr let me die!  \nThe child is father of the man;  \nAnd I could wish my days to be  \nBound each to each by natural piety.  </code>"
