    "innerHtml": "Lady Clare."
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "Girls always love \"Lady Clare\" and \"The Lord of Burleigh.\" They like to think that it is enough to be a splendid woman without title or wealth. They want to be loved, if they are loved at all, for their good hearts and graces of mind. Tennyson (1809-92 makes this point repeatedly through his poems.     )"
