  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "\"Hiawatha\" needs no commendation. Hundreds of thousands of children in our land know snatches of it It is a child's poem, every line of it. One summer in Boston more than 50,000 people went to take a peep at the poet's house. (1807-82.)"
