    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "\"A Farm-Yard Song\" was popular years ago with Burbank, the great reader. How the boys and girls loved it! The author, J. T. Trowbridge (1827-still living), \"is a boy-hearted man,\" says John Burroughs. The poem is just as popular as it ever was."
