    "tag": "blockquote",
    "innerHtml": "<p>ON TURNING UP HER NEST WITH THE PLOW, NOVEMBER, 1785\n\"To a Mouse\" and \"To a Mountain Daisy,\" by Robert Burns (1759-96), are the ineffable touches of tenderness that illumine the sturdy plowman. The contrast between the strong man and the delicate flower or creature at his mercy makes tenderness in man a vital point in character.</p>"
