  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "\"We build the ladder by which we climb\" is a line worthy of any poet. J. G. Holland (1819-81 has immortalised himself in this line, at least.     )"
  },
  {
    "tag": "pre",
    "innerHtml": "<code>Heaven is not reached at a single bound,  \nBut we build the ladder by which we rise  \nFrom the lowly earth to the vaulted skies,  \nAnd we mount to its summit round by round.  \n\nI count this thing to be grandly true:  \nThat a noble deed is a step toward God,—  \nLifting the soul from the common clod  \nTo a purer air and a broader view.  </code>"
  },
  {
