    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "\"The Burial of Sir John Moore\" was one of my reading-lessons when I was a child. A distinguished teacher says: \"It has become a part of popular education,\" as has also \"The Eve of Waterloo\" and \"The Death of Napoleon.\" They are all poems of great rhythmical swing, intense and graphic. (1791-1823.)"
