    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "\"Hervé Riel\" (by Robert Browning, 1812-89 is a poem for older boys. Here is a hero who does a great deed simply as a part of his day's work. He puts no value on what he has done, because he could have done no other way.     )"
